    <div id="otaku-paradise-website">
        <h2>Otaku Paradise (Website)</h2>
        <img src="/images/Otaku-Paradise-Laptop.png" alt="Otaku Paradise Index on Laptop">
        <br>
        <p>
            Otaku Paradise is a basic ecommerce website that specialises in sellings anime merchandise. 
            Users were not able to actual purchase any merchandise. The sites aim was to demonstrate 
            the basic skills that were taught in class. So, the site was more visual than practical. 
            Otaku Paradise was worked on for two iterations. The first iteration was originally a pure HTML, 
            CSS and JAVASCRIPT project for an introductory web development course done as a team as shown on 
            the About Us page. While the second iteration was done solo with PHP added to it. The PHP was to allow 
            login and sign up (profile), reviews and cart to be more practical and work rather than just visual. 
            The relevant data were saved to CSV files or session variables.
            <br><br>
            Languages Used:
            <li>Css</li>
            <li>Html</li>
            <li>JavaScript</li>
            <li>PHP</li>
        </p>
        <br>
        <p>
            Features of the Website:
            <li>Assortment of Items (One Per Category)</li>
            <li>Cart - One Item At A Time</li>
            <li>Email System - Uses Only Valid Emails to Send Emails To Me If I Have Accept From Secure Emails On</li>
            <li>Login/Sign-Up (Profile)</li>
            <li>Reviews For Items</li>
        </p>
